snippet.textDisplay: It’s interesting that the character in the second book is supposed to be black and the show is literally grounded around changing identities yet everyone wants Kinneman to play Kovac again. I get liking Kinneman’s acting style for Kovac but saying you don’t like Mackie in his other roles so you won’t like him in this role based off his features or previous roles is ridiculous because in those other roles he was playing another character so how are you basing his acting(which must be good to someone because he’s in a lot of movies including Avengers arguably the biggest movie ever while Kinneman is type casted and plays the same roles over and over) in this unreleased season, off his other roles. Just as when Cavil who played Superman was named as the actor for Geralt and everyone thought he would butcher the role but he is able to expand his acting across a diverse character list.  The  same thing could be said when they had the original Kovac make an appearance in season 1 after being used to seeing Kinneman play this character. Even I was a bit thrown off. But that is the whole point of changing sleeves. The casting is supposed to throw you off.  Kinneman playing a traumatized Kovac will be different than Mackie playing a more subdued Kovac who if you watched the last season dealt with his trauma at the end of season 1 and will not be the same Kovac we saw at the beginning of season 1. If you end up not liking the season based off the fact Kinneman isn’t in the lead role and Mackie is than go watch a show where you can see more of Kinneman.
